rComments: Professor Thompson was very concise and clear. I enjoyed his lectures and his use of powerpoint was very easy to study from. Even if you don't do the readings, the overhead sums it all up anyway. Wants nothing more than for students to do well. He is overall a very good Professor and young(er) and fresh. Great Guy!
Great prof.  Very knowledgeable.  Extremely clear.
loved every class with him. he tests what he teaches, you are never surprised and cursing him. i appreciate that. It has kept me confident and engaged.

Interesting course with a reasonable amount of reading. Excellent powerpoints that summarize the reading material. Marks are fair. Overall, a very enjoyable class with an excellent professor who knows what he's doing. No complaints =)
a pretty easy third year course. the material was just a rehashing of stuff covered in lower years. the paper topics were just as easy.

Great class, and a great prof. However, I never felt especially challenged... never had one of those "wow" moments (see Prof. John Vervaeke for example). But all around good job teaching a very tough though fascinating subject.
